Package: steinsampling
Title: Kernel Stein Discrepancy Goodness-of-Fit and Stein Sampling Tools
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-06-26
Authors@R: c(
    person("Junhao", "Gao",
           email = "jug049@ucsd.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Ery", "Arias-Castro",
           email = "eariascastro@ucsd.edu",
           role = "aut")
    )
Maintainer: Junhao Gao <jug049@ucsd.edu>
Description: Provides three Stein-discrepancy goodness-of-fit tests and several
    Stein-method-based sampling methods. The kernel Stein discrepancy (KSD)
    U-statistic test ('ksd_u_test.R') and KSD V-statistic test ('ksd_v_test.R')
    check whether samples match a target distribution,
    following Liu et al. (2016) <arXiv:1602.03253> and Chwialkowski et al.
    (2016) <arXiv:1602.02964>. The finite set Stein discrepancy (FSSD) test
    ('fssd_test.R') is a linear time goodness-of-fit test following
    Jitkrittum et al. (2017) <arXiv:1705.07673>. The sampling tools include
    Stein thinning ('stein_thinning.R') for selecting representative samples
    following Riabiz et al. (2022) <arXiv:2005.03952>, Stein Points
    ('stein_points.R') for constructing representative point sets following
    Chen et al. (2018) <arXiv:1803.10161>, Stein Point Markov chain Monte Carlo
    ('stein_point_mcmc.R') for MCMC-based Stein point selection following Chen
    et al. (2019) <arXiv:1905.03673>, and Stein variational gradient descent
    ('svgd.R') for deterministic particle-based variational inference following
    Liu and Wang (2016) <arXiv:1608.04471>. Gaussian mixture model (GMM)
    utilities ('gmm_model.R') create mixtures, draw samples, perturb component
    means, compute likelihoods, posterior component probabilities and score
    functions, and plot one-dimensional samples.
URL: https://github.com/junhao7622/Stein_Sampling
BugReports: https://github.com/junhao7622/Stein_Sampling/issues
Config/steinsampling/replication-data:
    Replication scripts are kept out of the CRAN testthat suite and stored in
    inst/replication/ in the source tree. Supporting size-limited data excerpts
    are stored in inst/replication/data/. After package installation, these
    files are available under system.file("replication", package =
    "steinsampling") and system.file("replication", "data", package =
    "steinsampling"). These scripts call the package through exported
    steinsampling functions. Complete external data sources are: LIBSVM Covertype
    <https://www.csie.ntu.edu.tw/~cjlin/libsvmtools/datasets/binary/covtype.libsvm.binary.scale.bz2>
    for 'covtype.libsvm.binary.scale.bz2' and its derived dense RDS file;
    Harvard Dataverse Goodwin/RW 'theta.csv'
    <https://dataverse.harvard.edu/api/access/datafile/4807844> and 'grad.csv'
    <https://dataverse.harvard.edu/api/access/datafile/4807838>; and SP-MCMC
    S&P 500 'data_spx.mat'
    <https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wilson-ye-chen/sp-mcmc/master/src/lib/data_spx.mat>.
